05111nam a22007575i 9780857451880DE-B159720221107062033.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221107t20112011nyu    fo  d z      eng d  a2011018717  a97808574518807 a10.1515/97808574518802doi  a(DE-B1597)636586  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anyucUS-NY00aHQ1194b.E27 2011 7aSOC0100002bisacsh00aEcofeminism and Rhetoric :bCritical Perspectives on Sex, Technology, and Discourse /ced. by Douglas A. Vakoch. 1aNew York; aOxford : bBerghahn Books, c[2011] 4c©2011  a1 online resource (186 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tFOREWORD -- tPREFACE -- tCHAPTER 1 The Rhetorics of Critical Ecofeminism: Conceptual Connection and Reasoned Response -- tCHAPTER 2 Into the Wild: An Ecofeminist Perspective on the Human Control of Canine Sexuality and Reproduction -- tCHAPTER 3 Gender Representations in Orangutan Primatological Narratives: Essentialist Interpretations of Sexuality, Motherhood, and Women -- tCHAPTER 4 Invitational Rhetoric: Alternative Rhetorical Strategy as Ecofeminist Practice for Transformation of Perception and Use of Energy in the Residential Built Environment from the Keweenaw to Kerala -- tCHAPTER 5 Ecofeminist Ethics and Digital Technology: A Case Study of Microsoft Word -- tAFTERWORD -- tEPILOGUE Unwrapping the Enigma of Ecofeminism: A Solution to the Illusion of Incoherence -- tNOTES ON CONTRIBUTORS -- tINDEX0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aBy drawing on the complex interplay of ecology and feminism, ecofeminists identify links between the domination of nature and the oppression of women. This volume introduces a variety of innovative approaches for advancing ecofeminist activism, demonstrating how words exert power in the world. Contributors explore the interconnections between the dualisms of nature/culture and masculine/feminine, providing new insights into sex and technology through such wide-ranging topics as canine reproduction, orangutan motherhood and energy conservation. Ecofeminist rhetorics of care address environmental problems through cooperation and partnership, rather than hierarchical subordination, encouraging forms of communication that value mutual understanding over persuasion and control. By critically examining ways that theory can help deconstruct domineering practices—exposing the underlying ideologies—a new generation of ecofeminist scholarship illuminates the transformative capacity of language to foster emancipation and liberation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aEcofeminism. 0aFeminist criticism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Feminism & Feminist Theory.2bisacsh1 aArmbruster, Karla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBile, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarr, Glynis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKindred, Merle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLockwood, Jeffrey A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMurphy, Patrick D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRomberger, Julia E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSowards, Stacey K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVakoch, Douglas A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVakoch, Douglas A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978085745188040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780857451880423Coveru